how_to_use: With eyes and mouth completely closed, press the pump firmly to evenly mist setting spray to face while holding bottle 10- to 12-inches away from skin.

reviews.headline: I didn't trust this, but...
reviews.comments: I didn't understand how this works, but this is now my makeup routine. It holds my makeup well all day.

reviews.headline: Amazing setting spray
reviews.comments: One of the best sprays withour alcohol i have tried. I am setting spray snob, usually stick with the skindinavia bridal spray, charlotte tilbury, one/size, and the hourglass veil. This MAC was earned a spot in my permanent rotation! It layers well, i like to spray throughout my routine and it does so perfectly. Also works great in companion with the CT airbrush spray. This melts powders with ease leaving your makeup with a more natural skin finish. Im quite oily, while im not sure it helps much with that but that doesnt bother me bc my makeup still looks great. Also the mister is perfect, very fine.

reviews.headline: Feel like getting waterboarded
reviews.comments: This was recommended to me by a prestige specialist in store and I believed her because her makeup was AH MAZING however when i got home and started using it the spray was so crazy and uneven I actually ended up ruining part if my nakeuo because it just unnecessarily soaked parts of my face. For a high end product you would think they wouid make sure it applies evenly.

reviews.headline: Amazing spray!
reviews.comments: Im a setting spray snob, I love the CT airbrush spray, one size, and the og skindinavia ones( the company that formulated urban decays). This gives a soft focus to my skin. Im oily and my tzone got shiny after about 3-4 hours but otherwise my makeup was flawless all thru a 12 hour busy day in a very humid climate. Excellent mist with no big droplets. Love that their is no alcohol in this formula, outpeforms many that do. Definitely earned a spot in my rotation and in my pro kit!

reviews.headline: Love MAC but don't love this
reviews.comments: The spray on this is too heavy. It should be a mist and this leaves your face with wet puddles.  Have to hold it super far from your face to even use it.

reviews.headline: Great hold
reviews.comments: Frequently order this item. Only challenge ai have noticed with the last few bottles is that the spray mist tends to "spit" and isn't a clean application even when adjusting distance. Packaging might need some work, but product is great!

reviews.headline: Not worth the hype
reviews.comments: Ive been testing this setting spray for months after getting it on sale and seeing all the positive reviews. First of all, im not a fan of the nozzle. It's not the worst but it's def not the best. It's a little more spitty than misty so I feel like I have to use more to get an even amount distributed. Of course, that just leaves me with super wet makeup that doesnt dry down well. Ive also tried spraying it on my face and then lightly tapping my face with a makeup sponge to absorb the excess spray and to help press it into my skin. It ended up lifting my makeup, my cream products were gone. Ive tried using it in between steps to help melt the products together but it takes too long to dry down and when i go on top with the next layer of makeup, it gets suuuuper patchy and it pills!!! I've also worn this with a face mask and it pilled all over my cheeks. Tiny little balls, ugh gross. I've never experienced pilling before and this is the only product that changed that. I have half a bottle left and i hate to waste it but I cannot for the life of me get it to work. I'm going back to Charlotte Tilbury

reviews.headline: Long lasting
reviews.comments:
I work 12 hour shifts and my make up stays on throughout it all. It's the best setting spray I have ever used. I would definitely recommend. It doesnt break me out or anything. I would definitely recommend.
I do use MAC power or foundation so I can't really speak to how it works with other foundations.

reviews.headline: Lasted during a half marathon!
reviews.comments: I LOVE this setting spray! I recently got back from doing the Princess Half Marathon weekend and this kept my make up in place during a 5k, 10k AND a half marathon in Disney! Highly recommend!

reviews.headline: If Pregnant Do Not Use!
reviews.comments: This should not be on shelves. Do not use especially if pregnant. Ingredients are harmful, hormone disruptors, and pollutants.

reviews.headline: I would not
reviews.comments: I personally did not like it. For the price of it, I thought it would be better.

reviews.headline: Excellent
reviews.comments: I like the formula.

reviews.headline: I love this setting spray
reviews.comments: Keeps my makeup put and flawless

reviews.headline: Feels like hairspray on your face, causes tight, dry skin
reviews.comments: My face looks dry and feels like I literally sprayed it with hairspray. Does it work? Yes, but I've tried several other brands and they never made my skin feel so uncomfortable like this brand does.

reviews.headline: Love it
reviews.comments: Makes my makeup last without changing how my makeup looks. My favorite out of all the ones I've tried, including One Size.

reviews.headline: The BEST setting spray!!!
reviews.comments: Most setting sprays in my opinion don't do much or anything at all‚Ä¶ However the MAC Fix +Stay Over keeps your make-up on perfectly, even on an over night airplane flight. Two thumbs up MAC!

reviews.headline: I would absolutely buy this product again!!
reviews.comments: This setting spray has seen me through crying jags, workouts, hot flashes etc. I can definitely rely on this to keep my makeup looking fresh throughout any day.

reviews.headline: Favorite setting spray
reviews.comments: This setting spray works so well to lock in my makeup and makes it last all day, and the reason its the spray I consistently reach for is because it doubles as a fixing spray. I spray it on at the end of my routine to lock everything in, and it also has the makeup melting benefits of the original Mac fix+ that make my beat look smoother and less textured.

reviews.headline: Definitely works
reviews.comments: Was out in the sun for about 4 hours. It was hot but my make up stayed flawless. Definitely will buy this again!

Don't put it on after the makeup!

faceoff_positive.comments: As a person who sweats very quickly, I have always shied away from wearing makeup so I don't mess it up or it doesn't melt off throughout the day. Going into this, I was not expecting the Mac Cosmetics Fix+ Stay Over Setting Spray to have a significant effect on my makeup look, but I wanted to put it to the test to see if it was really worth the hype. I decided to put on a face of makeup and seal it all with this setting spray for a day on set, and the results definitely lived up to the hype. It lasted through the outfit changes, standing in long lines in the mid-day heat, and our 12-hour day on set. I loved the moisturizing feeling it left on my skin which I guess is because there is no alcohol in it. This day on set, the Georgia heat was really working against us and my personal fan wasn't doing enough to keep the sweat off, so I started dabbing my face off with some paper towels. I stopped mid-way through because I forgot I was even wearing makeup, so I pulled my phone out to check my face and double-checked the paper towel itself just to see that nothing moved and everything was still set in place. I was in complete shock. Even coming home at the end of the day, I noticed that my makeup looked pretty good still in comparison to how it looked when I initially applied it. I was truly surprised by the performance of the Mac Cosmetics Fix+ Stay Over Setting Spray. It is safe to say I will start trying more makeup looks on a consistent basis with the help of this product.
faceoff_positive.headline: My new go-to setting spray
